atinx culture helped shape British post-punk. He traces the fandom networks that link these groups across space and time to illuminate how popular music establishes and facilitates intimate relations across the Atlantic. In so doing, he demonstrates how the music and styles that have come to define the 1980s hold significant sway over younger generations equally enthused by their matchlessly pleasurable and political reverberations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHispanic American gaysxSocial life and customsy20th century. 0aHispanic American youthxSocial life and customsy20th century. 0aPopular musicxLatin American influenceszGreat Britain. 0aPopular musicxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aPost-punk musicvCross-cultural studies. 0aYouthxSocial life and customsy20th centuryzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Hispanic American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL0 cprintz978147801858240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023180?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023180423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023180/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA